       The assessment enables us to objectify the communication difficulties you are experiencing, to identify your needs and intervention objectives with you and, finally, to suggest ways of remedying them. The assessment takes place over 1 to 3 meetings, depending on the area of concern.
    </p>

    <p>
        Assessment fees include the completion of assessment tasks, interpretation of results, transmission of results and writing of the assessment report and intervention plan.
    </p>

    <p>
        At the end of the assessment, a meeting is held to discuss the results and present the various intervention objectives based on the results and your projects. The means of intervention are also discussed.
    </p>

    <p>Intervention may help you achieve your goals in the future.</p>

