<TextContainer Title="Intervention">
    <p>
        Intervention can be aimed at promoting recovery of language functions, facilitating participation in daily activities or carrying out specific tasks. The frequency of meetings is determined together, based on our service agreement.
    </p>

    <p>
   Intervention can take place on an individual basis, with a loved one, or through group activities. We always work on the basis of your current interests and projects. I also work with people wishing to remain in the workplace, adapting the current environment and identifying strategies to compensate for language difficulties.
    </p>

    <p>
        At all times during the intervention, the relevance of the exercises to the objectives is clearly explained. The relationships between the various factors in your environment that can have an impact on your communication are also explained.
    </p>

    <p>During the intervention, more specific objectives are possible, targeting in particular:</p>

    <ul>
        <li>Oral expression: Finding words to speak, having a conversation, explaining, talking, discussing. </li>
        <li>Reading: Reading short stories, articles and novels. </li>
        <li>Writing: Writing SMS, e-mails, letters, essays. </li>
        <li>Alternative and augmentative communication: It is possible to find alternatives to speaking, reading or writing when faced with communication difficulties. </li>
        <li>Voice: Speaking with a better voice (stronger, less hoarse, less tiring). Better understanding of voice structure and mechanics.</li>
        <li>Swallowing: Making it easier to eat and easier to swallow. Better understanding of the structure and function of swallowing.</li>
    </ul>

